{
  "text": "Prevalence studies show that poultry can be colonized with C. difficile [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). In a cross-sectional study of poultry in Zimbabwe, the C. difficile culture prevalence was reported as 29% and, of the strains isolated, 90% were toxigenic [CITATION_3] ). However, these prevalence studies did not state the age of the chickens sampled and neither was there evidence of enteritis in the poultry. In addition, C. difficile has been reported in captive ostriches [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
